-- Russian Consul in Japan Dies After Accidental Fall Into Ravine
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2012-05-27T08:28:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-27/russian-consul-in-japan-dies-after-accidental-fall-into-ravine.html
Vladimir Pushkov, Russian consul
general in  Japan , died yesterday after falling into a 50-meter
(164-foot) deep ravine near Niigata, Rossiya 24 reported.  Pushkov slipped into the gully while playing volleyball
with friends at a picnic to celebrate his 55th birthday, the
state television channel reported. Another Russian diplomat
damaged his spine, Rossiya 24 said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
